    • Method Detail

      • parseAST

        public AbstractSyntaxAST parseAST(AbstractSyntaxAST parentAST,
                                  SyntaxAnalyzer syntaxAnalyzer)
        This method will parse the AbstractStatementAST and checks it for the correct syntax. This AST can be used by everything but some ASTs are different then others. So the ThisStatementAST will not accept a "this" keyword etc. Every statement needs to start with an IdentifierToken so they can be separated.
        Specified by:
        parseAST in class AbstractSyntaxAST
        Parameters:
        parentAST - The parent of the AST. With it you can check for correct usage of the statement.
        syntaxAnalyzer - The given SyntaxAnalyzer is used for checking the syntax of the current Token list.
        Returns:
        It will return null if an error occurred or an AbstractStatementAST if it parsed until to the end.

      • printSyntaxAST

        public void printSyntaxAST(java.io.PrintStream printStream,
                           java.lang.String indents)
        Description copied from class: AbstractSyntaxAST
        This method will be overwritten by the classes which extends AbstractSyntaxAST. It will print with help of the PrintStream and indents a tree which is used for debugging. To print all RootSyntaxASTs you just need to call this method ArkoiCompiler.printSyntaxTree(PrintStream).
        Specified by:
        printSyntaxAST in class AbstractSyntaxAST
        Parameters:
        printStream - the PrintStream which should get used for the output.
        indents - the indents which will make the AST look like a Tree.
